      "writtenOn": "2019-01-24T23:03:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah - I didn\u0027t see this before. Before there was a  \"display: none\" on the entire tabs div kept from showing any of this content (including the overview) until the jquery javascript got a chance to tabify it. If you look closely now you\u0027ll see this content render without the tabs briefly before getting tabified. On a fast computer this will be hard to see but it flashes briefly. I think you should still have a \"display: none\" on the containing div to avoid this flash.",
      "parentUuid": "dfe08f03_6ee50bd8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 102,
        "startChar": 28,
